node.text:
Please comment: Does money buy happiness?
---
🔑 Follow me, @smilingerik!⠀
---⠀
💫 I know rich people who are unhappy. It's safe to say that money isn't the only thing needed for happiness.

However, money can solve a lot of problems and give you more freedom in your life. 

That being said, if you want to be happy and you want to use money to get there. It's important that you use money the right way.

Use money to buy yourself more time, not stuff.
Use money to buy better health, not status.

It's easy to end up in a loop of buying expensive things, then having to work to pay for everything, then buy more things and just keep repeating. If you are in this loop, it doesn't matter how much money you make, it will never make you happy.

💫 My challenge for you today is to think about your expenses. Where do you spend money? Are you buying things to impress others, or are you spending your money to free up time to be with people you care about?

node.text:
I believe optimism is a super power - AND I believe it can be trained.

Practicing law of attraction, visualising and feeling the goals you have can be one way of training your mind to be more positive.

Another way is to end each day by writing down three things that have been good about this day:

- One thing about someone else that you are grateful for.
- One thing about yourself that you are proud of.
- One things about the day in general that you are happy it happened.

I've done this for years, and it has trained my mind to look for good things in others, good things in myself and good things about my day. It has made me a more positive and a happier person!

So the questions are, how would your life look if you were a more optimistic person? Would you like that life?
